@node Login Screen Desktop and Terminal
@chapter Login Screen, Desktop and Terminal
@cindex Login Screen, Desktop and Terminal
Examples are given with Ubuntu Linux. Other Linux distributions should be
similar.
@*
@*
Start the Linux computer and it will proceed to the login screen.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/LoginScreenCropped-960x576,12.5cm,7.5cm,Login Screen Linux,png}
@*
@*
Select the user name and enter the password.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/LoginScreenPasswordCropped-960x576,12.5cm,7.5cm,Login Screen Linux,png}
@*
@*
The Linux desktop will display.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/Desktop-960x576,,210pt,Desktop Linux Screen,png}
@*
@*
@center @image{images/2-960x576,,120pt,Picture of Bella,jpg}
@*
@*
We will proceed to open a Linux terminal. On the upper left hand side of the screen select Activities.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/Activities,,110pt,Activies,png}
@*
@*
A input box saying ``Type To Search'' box will appear.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/TypeToSearch,12cm,2.5cm,Type To Search,png}
@*
@*
Inside the ``Type To Search'' input box type the word Terminal.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/TypeToSearchTerminal,12cm,3.5cm,Activies,png}
@*
@*
The Linux terminal will appear.
@*
@*
@center @image{images/Terminal-960x576,12cm,7cm,Image of the Linux Terminal,png}
@*
@*
@center @image{images/3-960x576,,80pt,Picture of Bella,jpg}
@*
@*
Congratulations! You have logged into Linux and opened a Linux terminal on the desktop!

